data.name: BBQ Glazed Salmon with Roasted Sweet Potatoes and Green Beans
data.quickTastyDescription: A succulent BBQ glazed salmon served with sweet roasted potatoes and vibrant green beans, perfect for a healthy and satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Peel and cut the sweet potatoes into cubes, then toss them in olive oil, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Spread the sweet potatoes on a baking sheet and roast for 20 minutes.
While the sweet potatoes are roasting, prepare the salmon. Brush each fillet generously with BBQ sauce.
After 20 minutes, add the salmon fillets to the baking sheet with the sweet potatoes and roast for an additional 12-15 minutes until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.
In the last 5 minutes of cooking, add the green beans to the baking sheet, drizzling them with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
Once everything is cooked, serve the BBQ glazed salmon alongside the roasted sweet potatoes and green beans.
